sap.fe.macros.Contact.description:

sap.fe.macros.name: sap.fe.macros

sap.fe.macros.Chart.description: Macro for creating a Chart based on provided OData v4 metadata.
sap.fe.macros.Chart.constructorDescription:
Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getId id} : string
    • {@link #getCollection collection} : sap.ui.model.Context
    • {@link #getPresentation presentation} : sap.ui.model.Context
    • {@link #getData data} : string
    • {@link #getChartType chartType} : string
    • {@link #getHeader header} : string
    • {@link #getHeight height} : string (default: 400px)
    • {@link #getWidth width} : string (default: 1000px)
    • {@link #getSelectionMode selectionMode} : sap.chart.SelectionMode (default: NONE)
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.fe.macros.MacroMetadata#constructor sap.fe.macros.MacroMetadata} can be used as well.
sap.fe.macros.Chart.helpDescription: Macro for creating a Chart based on provided OData v4 metadata.

presentation.description: Metadata path to the presentation (UI.Chart w or w/o qualifier)
presentation.helpDescription: Metadata path to the presentation (UI.Chart w or w/o qualifier)

data.description: Binding information for chart - if not specified it is created from the metadata information
data.helpDescription: Binding information for chart - if not specified it is created from the metadata information

chartType.description: The chart type (Column, Bar, etc.) - if not specified chartType is picked from the metadata information
chartType.helpDescription: The chart type (Column, Bar, etc.) - if not specified chartType is picked from the metadata information

header.description: The header text of the chart - if not specified it is picked up from the metadata information
header.helpDescription: The header text of the chart - if not specified it is picked up from the metadata information

collection.description: Metadata path to the entitySet or navigationProperty
collection.helpDescription: Metadata path to the entitySet or navigationProperty

sap.fe.macros.Form.description:
Macro for creating a Form based on provided OData v4 metadata. Usage example: 
<macro:Form
 id="SomeID"
 entitySet="{entitySet>}"
 facet="{facet>}"
 formTitle="someTitle"
 editMode="Editable"
 createMode="true"
 useFormContainerLabels="true"
 partOfPreview="true"
 onChange=".handlers.onFieldValueChange"
/>

      • Term CollectionFacet
        Collection Facet
      • Term ReferenceFacet
        Reference Facet
      • Term PartOfPreview
        This Facet and all included Facets are part of the preview
      • Term Hidden
        The filter field will not be created
